ğŸ§ª Advanced Usage

ğŸ’¡ These features are powerful but not essential for getting started.

ğŸ“ Special Field Types

from laydata import SingleSelect, MultiSelect, Date, Attachment
from datetime import datetime

Employee = await Employees.add({
    "Department": SingleSelect("Engineering"),
    "Skills": MultiSelect(["Python", "React"]),
    "HireDate": Date(datetime(2023, 1, 15)),
    "ProfilePhoto": Attachment("https://example.com/photo.jpg")
})


â¸»

ğŸ›  Table Metadata Management

Tasks = await ProjectBase.table("Tasks", icon="ğŸ“‹", description="Task tracking")
await Tasks.update_icon("âœ…")
await Tasks.update_description("Updated description")

AllTables = await ProjectBase.tables()


â¸»

ğŸ“¦ Batch Operations & Error Handling

BatchData = [{"Name": f"Item {i}", "Price": 10 + i} for i in range(10)]

for item in BatchData:
    try:
        await Items.add(item)
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Failed: {e}")


â¸»

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ… Always use PascalCase for Space, Base, Table, and field names.
âœ… Treat records as objects â€” record.edit() and record.field() are the preferred ways to work with them.
âœ… Start with simple queries (where().all(), get_by()) and build up to more complex filters as needed.
âœ… Keep risky or infrequent operations (bulk deletes, update_icon) in dedicated functions or scripts.

